The brand features a portfolio of over 40 SKUs, including Low-Sugar, Sugar-Free, Immunity-Support, and Caffeinated Energy formulations. Initially gaining popularity through motivational water bottles in 2019, the business strategically pivoted in 2021 to consumable, subscription-based electrolyte products, recognizing the long-term sustainability of recurring revenue. The brand generates approximately 99% of its revenue from Amazon, achieving robust growth with a 65% year-over-year increase in revenue to $17.4M. The business’s primary manufacturer has existing capacity to immediately support a 1.5x–2x increase in production, with additional capacity to scale production up to 4x within 2–3 months, ensuring rapid growth potential. full_description: SBA PQ | 10-Yr-Old FBA, Category Best Seller | 13% Rev & 27% SDE YOY Growth | 78,000 Reviews | Quiet Light Sell Buy Learn About Success Stories Free Valuation All Amazon Ecommerce SaaS Content Membership Articles Podcasts Videos Guides About Us Partners Free Valuation SBA PQ | 10-Yr-Old FBA, Category Best Seller | 13% Rev & 27% SDE YOY Growth | 78,000 Reviews Currently Under Offer REVENUE $14,257,120 INCOME $2,978,291 MULTIPLE 3.5x Asking Price: $10,425,000 + Inventory Reading Time: 2 minutesThis SBA pre-qualified, 10-year-old FBA enterprise began selling on Amazon in late 2014. The owner has built a true category brand leader that only time, attention to detail, and success can create. They’ve amassed 78,000 positive reviews across 128 SKUs, 42,000 of which are for their top SKU, and they’ve enjoyed YoY revenue and SDE growth of 12.6% and 27.46% respectively. They’ve earned the Best Seller Badge in Grocery for their main product and multiple sub-300 BSRs (Best Sellers Ranks), all while offering their products at competitive prices (and even increasing prices in 2023–24). Over time, their listings reached the top of Amazon organic rankings in their category, and sales increased rapidly as a result. The company operates out of a fully equipped, 58K sq. ft. leased facility in the Northeast, where their team of ~25 employees assembles variety snack boxes and gift baskets under their private-label, trademarked brand, which they sell on Amazon and Shopify (95% and 5% of TTM revenue, respectively). All logistics are performed in-house between day and night shifts. Operations are lean and closely monitored by management for speed, accuracy, attendance, and quality, representing a true barrier to entry. Though the company has gained a large chunk of market share for their category, growth opportunities are apparent, including 1) creating more holiday-themed and year-round ASINs (with not much competition for quality holiday-themed gift products, the seller believes a new owner could generate an additional $2M in annual revenue if they execute this strategy), 2) performing social media and PPC marketing off Amazon, and 3) driving more traffic to Shopify. The owner currently spends ~30 hrs/wk managing the business remotely but does visit the warehouse a couple of times per month for 4 hrs/visit. The owner has been going full steam ahead for a decade and is ready to pull his chips off the table and reinvest the proceeds of the sale into commercial real estate. full_description: 7 Year Old Amazon FBA Shower Filter Business w/No Seasonality, Fantastic Reviews, & 25% Net Margins | Quiet Light Sell Buy Learn About Success Stories Free Valuation All Amazon Ecommerce SaaS Content Membership Articles Podcasts Videos Guides About Us Partners Free Valuation 7 Year Old Amazon FBA Shower Filter Business w/No Seasonality, Fantastic Reviews, & 25% Net Margins Currently Under Offer REVENUE $9,835,387 INCOME $2,427,197 MULTIPLE 4.2x Asking Price: $10,200,000 + Inventory Reading Time: 2 minutesLaunched in 2017, this business was created by seasoned Amazon ecosystem pros. After thorough research, the sellers discovered a very large market with a huge opportunity for improvement. At the time, most of the competition was selling a three-stage water filtration system. The sellers introduced a 10-stage, 15-stage, and eventually 20-stage filtration system that raised the bar for the entire Filtration industry. In fact, Better Homes and Gardens ranked their shower heads first for best shower filter in 2023. One of the founders has a background in chemistry, which allowed them to test and ensure that each filtration state is scientifically validated. In addition to the 20-stage filter, they offer filters that add various vitamins to the water. With this business, a buyer is presented with the opportunity to acquire a thriving brand in a large niche and grow the business through expanded product offerings and more focus on subscription customers. One exciting operational trend is the steady nature of the business month after month. It is rare to find a business without a busy season or a slow season. Because the cartridges need to be replaced, the sellers believe that about 40%–50% of their sales each year come from repeat purchases. They believe in their product so much that they encourage customers to get a free water report through an easy form on their website. The sellers recommend having a 3PL located on the West Coast, ideally in California. The business requires 30,000 sq. ft. of space to allow for shipping to Amazon FBA. They also recommend partnering with a 3PL that can handle FBM orders as this provides the best mix of options to manage business logistics. The business operates primarily through two sales channels—their Shopify store and Amazon—generating approximately $1.7 million in annual revenue (post Amazon/Shopify fees). Shopify brings in about $1M in revenue, while Amazon grosses about $800K. The headbands account for just under 50% of revenue and nearly 100% of Amazon revenue. Over the last two years, they have shifted to swimsuits. Each of the past two seasons, they have experienced stockouts on their best-sellers. Shopify AOV (average order value) is currently $90 but increases throughout the swim season, and customer acquisition cost (through Meta) stands at $35. The email list has 50,000 subscribers, and the brand has 10,000 SMS subscribers. Most marketing is focused on Meta advertising and influencers. The company has 98K followers on Instagram and 29K on Facebook. Growth opportunities include listing the full product line on Amazon, wholesale expansion, custom co-branded headbands, and correct inventory forecasting (they’ve run out of best-sellers each swim season). The owners have operated the business as a lifestyle business for years while spending a combined 15–20 hours weekly managing all aspects of the business. As a lean, efficiently operated business with minimal overhead, this company presents an opportunity for an entrepreneurial buyer to acquire a stable brand with established systems and significant growth potential. full_description: Patented FBA Pet Travel Brand | 2,700+ 4.5-Star Reviews | Proven Market Fit | Huge Growth Potential | Quiet Light Sell Buy Learn About Success Stories Free Valuation All Amazon Ecommerce SaaS Content Membership Articles Podcasts Videos Guides About Us Partners Free Valuation Patented FBA Pet Travel Brand | 2,700+ 4.5-Star Reviews | Proven Market Fit | Huge Growth Potential REVENUE $201,719 INCOME $6,757 MULTIPLE 11.84x Asking Price: $80,000 Reading Time: < 1 minuteFounded in 2016, this category-defining Pet Travel brand offers innovative dog car seat covers with a patented mesh window design. This unique feature addresses pet anxiety by maintaining visual contact between dogs and owners while providing enhanced safety during travel. With over 2,700 positive reviews and a 4.5-star Amazon rating, the brand has demonstrated exceptional product-market fit in the growing Pet Accessories segment. This Amazon Brand Registered business presents a compelling acquisition opportunity centered around its US design patent (valid until 2034). An estimated 40%–50% of competitors now incorporate similar designs, creating two powerful advantages: the ability to enforce patent rights to reduce competition and generate passive income through licensing agreements. Previous enforcement efforts have already yielded nearly $50,000 in royalty settlements. The owners have intentionally scaled back operations since October 2023 due to external circumstances affecting them in Israel. Despite this temporary slowdown, the fundamentals remain strong with an efficient FBA operation, established suppliers in China, and a loyal customer base. Growth opportunities are obvious, with international expansion showing particular promise. A recent test campaign in Canada generated $12,000 in sales from just $2,500 in advertising spend (20.8% total advertising cost of sales [TACOS]), outperforming US metrics with minimal localization. The business currently operates almost exclusively on Amazon, creating significant opportunities for channel diversification to Walmart, Chewy, and direct-to-customer platforms. For an experienced ecommerce operator, immediate optimization opportunities include automated PPC tools, product line expansion, and strategic patent enforcement—all clear pathways to substantial, defensible growth. The owners are selling due to the effects of the ongoing conflict in Israel and a lack of capital and resources to sustain the company. full_description: Home Services Franchises for Sale – BizQuest Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker My Account Dashboard My Saved Businesses My Saved Searches Sign Out Sign Up / Sign In Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker Sign Up Sign In Franchise Directory Home Services Franchises – BizQuest Home Services Franchises for Sale Buy a Home Services Franchise Today When deciding what sort of franchise to buy, home services franchises should be at the top of your list to consider. These businesses provide professional services to customers in the comfort of their home. As people's lives become increasingly busy, using a home services business to help with tasks such as cleaning the house or mowing the lawn is becoming a popular option for consumers. A few popular home services franchises include Furniture Medic, Lawn Doctor and Pack It Movers. Read more Choosing to buy a home services franchise will give you and your employees the potential to become close with members of your community. Customers will see the appeal of being able to contact your business and have a service provided in the comfort of their home. Since home services businesses are valued so highly, many people will need these services and you’ll have the opportunity to create a solid base of clients who may become repeat customers. You’ll also get to see a quick difference after you provide your service, whether your business focuses on lawn care, designing accessible spaces or making a repair on a home, and will know that you’ve tangibly improved people’s lives. Franchising a business can be a great financial opportunity. However, before making any final decisions, it’s important to take your time researching your options. Franchising a well-established business can provide you with customers already loyal to the company, and you’ll have less to worry about than you would with starting your own business. However, choosing to franchise a smaller home services franchise for sale can give you the opportunity to build the brand and put your own twist on the process. No matter what type of home services business you franchise, your business has the potential to become a staple of your community and will prove to be a successful investment. "addressLocality": null, "addressRegion": "Available in Wyoming"}}}}}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 58, "item": {"@type": "Person", "name": "Gregg Kunz, CBI, M&AMI, Master CBI", "description": "Rocky Mountain Business Advisors is located in Denver, and we help business owners in the Denver metro area, and throughout Colorado and Wyoming, sell their businesses. \r\n\r\nIf you\u00e2\u0080\u0099re ready to sell now, we can work to make that happen quickly, on the terms you want and need. If you\u00e2\u0080\u0099re not quite ready to sell, we can assist you with implementing strategies and improvements that could significantly increase the value of your business by the time you do want to exit.\r\n\r\nWe have a database of serious, qualified buyers who might be interested in your business, and we sell all types of businesses, including the trades, services, manufacturing, distribution, retail, tech, and e-commerce businesses.\r\n\r\nIf you have a well-run business, with strong management, effective processes, and healthy, organized financials, let\u00e2\u0080\u0099s get you the compensation you deserve for everything you\u00e2\u0080\u0099ve put into the business and the sacrifices you\u00e2\u0080\u0099ve made\r\n\r\nWe are highly focused on buyer targeting and identification especially with niche and unique businesses which other firms may prefer not to engage with. We are industry agnostic, preferring to work across multiple and varied industries where strong management, organized financials, and a commitment to process are hallmarks of the business.", "url": "https://www.bizquest.com/business-broker/rocky-mountian-business-advisors/gregg-kunz-cbi-mandami-master-cbi/BW36380/", "jobTitle": "BUSINESS BROKER", "image": "https://images.bizquest.com/shared/brokerdirectory/images/36380/lg_prs_Gregg_Kunz_Headshot.jpg", "address": [{"@type": "PostalAddress", "addressLocality": "Laramie County", "addressRegion": " WY"}], "worksFor": {"@type": "Organization", "name": "Rocky Mountian Business Advisors", "description": "At Rocky Mountain Business Advisors, we help owners sell their businesses for the highest price possible, in the shortest amount of time. We also negotiate favorable terms for sellers and have a proven process that helps ensure a smooth transfer of ownership.\r\n\r\nWith more than 20 years experience, we focus on selling privately-held businesses with $500,000 to $20 million (or more) in revenues. Over the years, the key to our success has been combining a process-oriented approach, sense of urgency, and commitment to protecting owners\u00e2\u0080\u0099 legacies.\r\n\r\nFree Consultation For Sellers\r\nIf you\u00e2\u0080\u0099d like to sell your business, we\u00e2\u0080\u0099re happy to offer a free consultation. In the consultation, we\u00e2\u0080\u0099ll talk about your business, your goals, and what you\u00e2\u0080\u0099d like to get out of the sale.\r\n\r\nValuing Your Business\r\nIf we\u00e2\u0080\u0099re a good fit and you decide to hire us as your business broker, we\u00e2\u0080\u0099ll complete a comprehensive valuation of your business. The valuation will include measures you can take to increase the value of the business and/or make the sale more appealing to a larger pool of buyers.\r\n\r\nGetting To Know You And Your Business \r\nWe\u00e2\u0080\u0099ll also make it our business to know your business and your markets, so that we can clearly articulate not only your financials, but also your unique value-drivers to potential buyers.\r\n\r\nMinimizing Distractions\r\nSelling a business, if you\u00e2\u0080\u0099re not careful, can be a giant distraction, and the longer the process drags on, the more it can devalue your business. From start to finish, we have a proven process that will enable you to run your business as usual, while we work behind the scenes to secure the sale.\r\n\r\nQualifying And Understanding Buyers\r\nOne of the primary ways that we minimize distractions is by pre-qualifying buyers, so that you don\u00e2\u0080\u0099t get your hopes up and waste time on someone who is unlikely to buy your business on your terms. Thanks to years of corporate senior management experience in starting, growing, owning, and selling companies, we have a process of evaluating buyers that helps ensure they have the financial resources to buy your business and the experience and skills to keep it running. \r\n\r\nGetting You What You Want\r\nMost potential business sales break down at the negotiating table, but we have the experience and expertise to make even the most complicated deals result in terms that you and the buyer can accept.\r\n\r\nYou\u00e2\u0080\u0099re Our Priority\r\nMany business brokers take pride in having a high number of listings of businesses for sale. We\u00e2\u0080\u0099re not like most brokers. By intention, we limit the number of owners we work with so that we can give you and your business the time, effort, and resources needed to ensure a successful sale.\r\n\r\nWhat Makes Us Successful? \r\nWe make it our business to know your business and the markets in which you operate so that we can clearly articulate not only the financials but as important, the unique value-drivers that Buyers always seek but which many Brokers fail to take the time to understand and convey to prospective Buyers. \r\nWhile most Business Brokers pride themselves on how many listings they have in their inventory we believe that it is in the best interests of our clients to limit the number of our listings so that our time, effort, and resources are focused on a small set of high-quality businesses. \r\n\r\nAre There Any Engagements We Do Not Accept?\r\nAmong the types of businesses that we do not accept as clients: those that are unable to substantiate their financials, are not cash flow positive, start-ups, or sellers that are unrealistic about the market value of their business (because these businesses rarely sell, and we are business brokers in the business of selling businesses \u00e2\u0080\u0093 not listing businesses).", "logo": "https://images.bizquest.com/shared/brokerdirectory/images/36380/lg_cmp_RMBA_Logo-PrintJPG.jpg"}}}]}

full_description: Cleaning & Maintenance Franchises for Sale – BizQuest Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker My Account Dashboard My Saved Businesses My Saved Searches Sign Out Sign Up / Sign In Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker Sign Up Sign In Franchise Directory Cleaning & Maintenance Franchises – BizQuest Cleaning & Maintenance Franchises for Sale Buy a Cleaning or Maintenance Franchise Today Buying a cleaning and maintenance franchise for sale has many benefits. For starters, nearly every person or business will need a cleaning service at some point. While some industries inherently focus on a limited clientele, a cleaning and maintenance company can be marketed to multiple demographics. The cleaning industry should also continue to grow over the next few years. Allied Market Research recently concluded that the global cleaning services market will reach $74.299 million by the year 2022. That is due to an expected increase in both commercial demand and consumers' disposable income. Read more Cleaning and maintenance franchises take a variety of forms. Some of these brands emphasize typical house or apartment cleaning. Other companies provide commercial cleaning services for office facilities. There are also franchises that include restoration cleaning services, junk removal, or even dry cleaning. Restoration cleaning has become particularly important in recent years due to climate change and the increasing number of natural disasters, such as hurricanes, earthquakes and tornados. If you choose to buy a cleaning and maintenance franchise, you will automatically have some advantages over your non-franchise competitors. For starters, you will be in charge of a business that already has a solid reputation and name recognition. You will not have to worry about making your company stand out in a crowded field. In addition, the franchisor often provides numerous services to its franchisees, including training and site selection. Some franchisors even help their business owners secure funding and buy necessary equipment. This gives franchisees less to worry about as they prepare to open their doors. Once your franchise does launch, you should get plenty of support and advice from your franchisor, and from other franchisees within the system. Of course, just like with any business venture, there is still some risk involved in buying a franchise. However, franchisors have the incentive to help their franchisees succeed. To have more control over both your day-to-day operations as well as the long term plan, consider buying a commercial cleaning and janitorial business for sale. Over 300 franchise owners! Open within 90 days!", "url": "https://www.bizquest.com/senior-helpers-franchise-for-sale/", "productId": "330", "offers": {"@type": "Offer", "price": 50000, "priceCurrency": "USD", "availability": "http://schema.org/InStock", "url": "https://www.bizquest.com/senior-helpers-franchise-for-sale/", "image": "https://images.bizquest.com/fnw/images/330/330/f523b714-1bb4-41ea-9109-8accb494d87e.jpg", "priceSpecification": null, "availableAtOrFrom": {"@type": "Place", "address": {"@type": "PostalAddress", "addressLocality": null, "addressRegion": "Available Nationwide"}}}}}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 58, "item": {"@type": "Person", "name": "Jay Whitney", "description": "TOP TEN MISTAKES CHILDCARE CENTER BUSINESS OWNERS MAKE WHEN SELLING THEIR CENTERS\r\n\r\nSelling a childcare center business is often a confusing and difficult process, and most business owners only do it once in a lifetime. Very few go through the process enough to really become comfortable with the ins and outs of selling a center successfully. \r\n\r\nA childcare center is a special use property and the best use for the real estate is as a childcare business. Potential buyers need to completely understand of the business before they buy the center. Very few brokers understand the childcare business enough so to increase the likelihood that a center will sell, and to potentially increase the value of the center.\r\n\r\nI, Jay Whitney, provide Business Sales Consulting and Loan Broker services to childcare center sellers. I have helped people sell and buy over 100 childcare centers. Here is my list of the top ten major mistakes that childcare business owners should avoid when it\u00e2\u0080\u0099s time to take an exit.\r\n\r\n10. NOT PLANNING FOR SALE. Planning for a sale, and taking actions on those plans, over the 2 to 3 years before an expected sale can often increase the sales price and after-tax proceeds of a sale by a VERY significant amount. Often, just spending a few months to improve the center before starting the marketing process can increase the value of a center.\r\n\r\n9. NOT SELLING WHEN YOU ARE BURNT OUT AND IT IS UNLIKELY THAT YOU WILL REGAIN THE RIGHT MOTIVATION to better your business. I have seen too many business owners who have rejected good offers only to see their business values decrease over the next few years.\r\n\r\n8. SELLING WHEN YOU ARE BURNT OUT, BUT, YOU BELIEVE THAT YOU CAN REGAIN THE RIGHT MOTIVATION to improve the valuation of your business. I have seen many business owners sell only to have a buyer who is motivated to improve the business do exactly that .... and double profits within a few years.\r\n\r\n7. USING A BROKER WITH A HIGH BROKER COMMISSION TO FIND BUYERS. 80% of all operating childcare center sales are NOT through a broker. Contacting existing childcare owners confidentially through a Business Sales Consultant (paid hourly) will save the seller 75% to 90% of typically high broker commissions. Using a consultant who understands the childcare center industry is far more effective than using a broker who is not experienced with the childcare industry to attract buyers because the consultant understand exactly what buyers are looking for when thinking of buying a center.\r\n\r\n6. NOT KNOWING THE BUSINESS VALUE OF THE CENTER. Too many business owners believe that their centers are worth far more than the price any buyer would reasonably pay. Therefore, when they get a great offer, they don't sell. (See mistake #9).\r\n\r\n5. ONLY ADVERTISING THE \"CHILDCARE CENTER FOR SALE\" TO THE POTENTIAL BUYERS WHO ARE CURRENTLY ACTIVELY LOOKING TO BUY a center instead of ALL the potential buyers. (Many existing childcare center owners want to buy an additional center, but, they are too busy managing their center to be always ACTIVELY searching for a center to buy. Childcare center owners (who are not direct competitors) should always be contacted.)\r\n\r\n4. NOT HAVING A \"CONFIDENTIAL SELLING DOCUMENT\" that covers, in detail, all the reasons why the center is valuable to buyers and how a buyer can improve the center. Each buyer needs to know that all other potential buyers are aware of all the opportunities to improve the center or else each buyer's offer will likely only consider the center's historical profits and not the opportunities to increase profits.\r\n\r\n3. NOT BEING PREPARED FOR DUE DILIGENCE - Every business acquisition process includes a due diligence phase where the acquirer examines all the documents and details to make sure that they are getting what they are paying for with no nasty surprises. All sellers should prepare for this by conducting a pre-due diligence review to identify and correct (or explain in the Selling Documents) any potential \"nasty surprises\" before the buyer finds them.\r\n\r\nThe goal of a buyer\u00e2\u0080\u0099s due diligence exam is to confirm if the information that the seller provided to the buyer BEFORE the offer is accurate and identify any unknown negative issues not communicated by the seller. A detailed due diligence examination looks at bank statements, credit card statements, detailed General Ledger, ProCare records (or whatever system the seller uses), food program & DFCS reports, attendance records, payroll records, etc. These documents are compared to tax and financial reports to confirm the financial information.\r\n\r\nThe worst thing for a seller is that buyer\u00e2\u0080\u0099s due diligence exam identifies negative issues that cause the buyer to reconsider their offer price and either renegotiate the price down, or cancel the acquisition. This can waste lots of the seller\u00e2\u0080\u0099s time as the sales process has to start back from scratch.\r\n\r\n2. NOT GETTING THE CENTER PRE-QUALIFIED FOR A SBA LOAN, OR GETTING IT PRE-QUALIFIED WITH THE WRONG LENDER BEFORE YOU APPROACH POTENTIAL BUYERS. The difference in monthly loan payment between a low and a high interest SBA loan can be as high as $1,400 for a $1 million loan. When a buyer expects a lower monthly loan payment when the price is being negotiated (because it was prequalified for financing), a buyer is more willing to offer more for the center. \r\n\r\nThere are about 6k SBA lenders. Each lender is different in terms of: 1) what loan amounts they like to lend, 2) what industries they like and dislike to lend to, 3) what interest rates that like to lend at, 4) what collateral requirements they require, and 5) what experience, credit score, and liquidity after a business is acquired they want the buyer to have. Most buyers do not know which SBA lenders have made many loans to childcare centers at low interest rates, and are therefore are the best lenders to initially contact to get financing. Therefore, many buyers can waste a considerable amounts of time with the wrong lender only for the loan request to be rejected; or the buyer get unfavorable loan terms (and tries to renegotiate to lower the price and/or increase the amount of seller financing). A buyer could also try to find a new lender (therefore the transaction closing date will be delayed).\r\n\r\n(Seller should use a Loan Broker who specializes in the childcare industry to pre-qualify the center to the best lenders early in the selling process to prevent Mistake #2)\r\n\r\n1. THE SINGLE BIGGEST MISTAKE A BUSINESS OWNER CAN MAKE IS ACCEPTING AN OFFER THAT SEEMS FAIR OR EVEN REALLY ATTRACTIVE WITHOUT THE PROPER PREPARATION. When you accept an offer and establish exclusivity with a single potential buyer and begin to iron out the details, you are stuck and you have little leverage in the negotiations that occurs between the initial acceptance of an offer and the transaction closing a few months later. The good offer that you start with never goes up, but it can easily go down as the process unfolds. You may be watching the price grow smaller because of the buyer's due diligence investigation. (See mistakes #3 & #4)\r\n\r\nFor information on getting started with Business Sales Consulting services, Business Acquisition Consulting services, or Loan Brokerage services for childcare centers, contact:\r\nJayWhitney@ChildcareBrokers.com 770-410-7582\r\n\r\nSee the Childcare Brokers website for:\r\nTOP NINE MISTAKES CHILDCARE CENTER BUSINESS BUYERS MAKE WHEN BUYING A CENTER", "url": "https://www.bizquest.com/business-broker/childcare-brokers/jay-whitney/BW868/", "jobTitle": "BUSINESS BROKER", "image": "https://images.bizquest.com/shared/brokerdirectory/images/868/lg_prs_JayWhitney2018HDR-2.jpg", "address": [{"@type": "PostalAddress", "addressLocality": "Cook County", "addressRegion": " IL"}], "worksFor": {"@type": "Organization", "name": "Childcare Brokers", "description": "We provide the following services for childcare center clients.\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Childcare center business sales & business acquisition consultants. (Have helped 100+ people sell/buy centers) \r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Loan brokers for childcare centers.(Have helped 100+ people get financing)\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Business Valuations (Have provided 200+ valuations)\r\n\r\nThe true benefits of a good Sell-Side Business Consultant (not BROKER) is helping the Owner/Seller:\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo sell the childcare center at the RIGHT price\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tBy recommending AGAINST selling NOW if exit planning shows it would be better to wait before selling\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo recommend against the seller from selling at a price below what the childcare center is worth\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo prevent the childcare center from languishing on the \u00e2\u0080\u009cbusiness for sale\u00e2\u0080\u009d marketplace for years\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo allow the business owner to have time to manage his/her business so that the business value does not suffer by helping in the many tasks required during the business sales process.\r\n\r\nThe true benefits of a good Buy-Side Business Acquisition Consultant and Buy-Side Business Loan Broker is helping the childcare business buyer:\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo find childcare center business owners who are truly motivated to sell. (Most childcare center owners who want to sell, are not listed for sale by business brokers. I can help you contact them by coaching you with the most effective approaches!)\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo find the RIGHT business to buy\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo prevent a client from over-paying for a business and/or buy the WRONG business\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo secure a SBA loan at a lower interest rate than what the buyer could get on his/her own.", "logo": ""}}}]}

full_description: Home Based Franchises for Sale – BizQuest Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker My Account Dashboard My Saved Businesses My Saved Searches Sign Out Sign Up / Sign In Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker Sign Up Sign In Franchise Directory Home Based Franchises – BizQuest Home Based Franchises for Sale Buy a Home Based Franchise Today Deciding to buy a home based business franchise can be lifechanging. Having a flexible schedule without a commute is a dream some people thing is impossible. With proper research and a well laid plan, owning a home based business franchise is possible and profitable. There are a multitude of creative businesses out there that have the potential to flourish when franchised. A potential owner needs to figure out what interests them and what they're good at to find a profitable match. There are companies like Aussie Pet Mobile that already have an advertising campaign and a client base intact. Fresh Coat is another intriguing business that has a computer system to make booking clients easy and stress free. There are a variety of options for those interested in finding a promising home based business franchise for sale. Read more Buying a franchise can be a way to get experience in the world of business ownership. The franchisor provides the system and training for the business and the buyer can learn from an already established business model. Franchises also tend to have a greater rate of success than other businesses like startups. In most cases, buying a franchise is less costly than starting a business from scratch and can provide the freedom of small-business ownership from the comfort of home. One of the greatest benefits of buying a home based franchise is that the buyer is purchasing an already proven business model. The advertising, product testing and business plan has already been executed. The key is for the buyer to find a franchise that fits their ambition and goals and be flexible in working with the larger brand. Prospective buyers can gain advice from other franchisees and set realistic expectations about what running and expanding a franchise will be like. full_description: Restaurant Franchises for Sale – BizQuest Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker My Account Dashboard My Saved Businesses My Saved Searches Sign Out Sign Up / Sign In Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker Sign Up Sign In Franchise Directory Restaurant Franchises – BizQuest Food & Restaurant Franchises for Sale Buy a Food or Restaurant Franchise Today For those interested in franchising opportunities, one of the best options is to buy a food and restaurant franchise. The demand for franchise restaurants is increasing, thanks to millennials’ love of convenience. Another positive aspect is the rise of third-party food delivery services facilitating even greater growth for some restaurants. These factors make purchasing a food-related franchise an enticing choice. Read more Starting a business takes courage and hard work, but opening a franchise can help simplify the process. Anyone who buys a franchise receives the benefits of others’ efforts in developing and promoting the brand. Most of the trial and error is complete, leaving behind a clear path to stable profit, as well as organizational support along the way. Of course, there is still enough uncertainty involved to keep the franchise owner motivated to achieve more. Whether the buyer’s goal is to alleviate risk or to undertake a challenge, acquiring a franchise is a suitable course of action. A quick search for a food and restaurant franchise for sale will yield an interesting array of obtainable eating establishments and other food-related businesses. The variety in the food industry is more than enough to match any entrepreneur’s lifestyle and interests. For example, if the potential purchaser is a night owl, there are late-night options such as Beerhead Bar and Eatery. Conversely, a breakfast and lunch restaurant like omelet specialist Squeeze In is ideal for those who prefer early morning hours. There are also options for business people who prefer not to own a traditional restaurant. Healthier 4U Vending and mobile kitchen supplier Pro Chef are examples of such choices. Of course, traditional restaurant franchise opportunities from companies such as Checkers or well-known options like Mrs. Fields Cookies are available as well. The food industry is full of diverse and rewarding franchise possibilities. If franchises aren't exactly what you're looking for, consider investing in food and beverage businesses for sale, that may allow you to have a bigger say in the direction and goals of your business. full_description: Healthcare and Senior Care Franchises for Sale – BizQuest Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker My Account Dashboard My Saved Businesses My Saved Searches Sign Out Sign Up / Sign In Buy a Business Buy a Franchise Sell a Business Knowledge Center Find a Broker Sign Up Sign In Franchise Directory Healthcare and Senior Care Franchises – BizQuest Healthcare & Senior Care Franchises for Sale Buy a Healthcare or Senior Care Franchise Today Purchasing a senior services franchise for sale is a great way to enter the business world. While buying any franchise carries inherent risks, senior services companies will continue to grow over the next few decades. That is because millions of baby boomers around the country are getting to the age where they require additional care. As a result, studies say the elder care industry is expected to bring in nearly $400 billion in revenue this year. That number should only increase in the coming years. The 2014 U.S. Census concluded that there will be 83.7 million Americans ages 65 and older in 2050. Read more These retirees will require specific needs. That is where senior care franchises come into play. Companies such as Golden Heart Senior Care provide a variety of non-medical services, from cleaning and cooking to meal planning and personal hygiene. Others, including Right at Home or Flextime Nurses, offer trained nurses who can administer certain medications. Many senior services businesses even include respite care for full-time caregivers who need a break from their daily duties. These are all valuable services that make owning a senior care franchise particularly rewarding. Before you buy a senior services franchise, there are certain things you should know. Purchasing a franchise is not like starting a business on your own. The franchisor has specific policies that you will have to follow. Still, this is a small price to pay for the assistance you will get from that corporation. The company will help you get your business up and running and may even provide training or financing. The franchisor also is usually willing to give out tips or suggestions whenever you need them. In addition, franchisors have a proven brand with a built-in customer base. So you will not have to spend much of your budget on advertising. Instead, you will have more money for other aspects of your business. For another experience with business ventures, consider researching and buying a health and medical business for sale. Very few go through the process enough to really become comfortable with the ins and outs of selling a center successfully. \r\n\r\nA childcare center is a special use property and the best use for the real estate is as a childcare business. Potential buyers need to completely understand of the business before they buy the center. Very few brokers understand the childcare business enough so to increase the likelihood that a center will sell, and to potentially increase the value of the center.\r\n\r\nI, Jay Whitney, provide Business Sales Consulting and Loan Broker services to childcare center sellers. I have helped people sell and buy over 100 childcare centers. Here is my list of the top ten major mistakes that childcare business owners should avoid when it\u00e2\u0080\u0099s time to take an exit.\r\n\r\n10. NOT PLANNING FOR SALE. Planning for a sale, and taking actions on those plans, over the 2 to 3 years before an expected sale can often increase the sales price and after-tax proceeds of a sale by a VERY significant amount. Often, just spending a few months to improve the center before starting the marketing process can increase the value of a center.\r\n\r\n9. NOT SELLING WHEN YOU ARE BURNT OUT AND IT IS UNLIKELY THAT YOU WILL REGAIN THE RIGHT MOTIVATION to better your business. I have seen too many business owners who have rejected good offers only to see their business values decrease over the next few years.\r\n\r\n8. SELLING WHEN YOU ARE BURNT OUT, BUT, YOU BELIEVE THAT YOU CAN REGAIN THE RIGHT MOTIVATION to improve the valuation of your business. I have seen many business owners sell only to have a buyer who is motivated to improve the business do exactly that .... and double profits within a few years.\r\n\r\n7. USING A BROKER WITH A HIGH BROKER COMMISSION TO FIND BUYERS. 80% of all operating childcare center sales are NOT through a broker. Contacting existing childcare owners confidentially through a Business Sales Consultant (paid hourly) will save the seller 75% to 90% of typically high broker commissions. Using a consultant who understands the childcare center industry is far more effective than using a broker who is not experienced with the childcare industry to attract buyers because the consultant understand exactly what buyers are looking for when thinking of buying a center.\r\n\r\n6. NOT KNOWING THE BUSINESS VALUE OF THE CENTER. Too many business owners believe that their centers are worth far more than the price any buyer would reasonably pay. Therefore, when they get a great offer, they don't sell. (See mistake #9).\r\n\r\n5. ONLY ADVERTISING THE \"CHILDCARE CENTER FOR SALE\" TO THE POTENTIAL BUYERS WHO ARE CURRENTLY ACTIVELY LOOKING TO BUY a center instead of ALL the potential buyers. (Many existing childcare center owners want to buy an additional center, but, they are too busy managing their center to be always ACTIVELY searching for a center to buy. Childcare center owners (who are not direct competitors) should always be contacted.)\r\n\r\n4. NOT HAVING A \"CONFIDENTIAL SELLING DOCUMENT\" that covers, in detail, all the reasons why the center is valuable to buyers and how a buyer can improve the center. Each buyer needs to know that all other potential buyers are aware of all the opportunities to improve the center or else each buyer's offer will likely only consider the center's historical profits and not the opportunities to increase profits.\r\n\r\n3. NOT BEING PREPARED FOR DUE DILIGENCE - Every business acquisition process includes a due diligence phase where the acquirer examines all the documents and details to make sure that they are getting what they are paying for with no nasty surprises. All sellers should prepare for this by conducting a pre-due diligence review to identify and correct (or explain in the Selling Documents) any potential \"nasty surprises\" before the buyer finds them.\r\n\r\nThe goal of a buyer\u00e2\u0080\u0099s due diligence exam is to confirm if the information that the seller provided to the buyer BEFORE the offer is accurate and identify any unknown negative issues not communicated by the seller. A detailed due diligence examination looks at bank statements, credit card statements, detailed General Ledger, ProCare records (or whatever system the seller uses), food program & DFCS reports, attendance records, payroll records, etc. These documents are compared to tax and financial reports to confirm the financial information.\r\n\r\nThe worst thing for a seller is that buyer\u00e2\u0080\u0099s due diligence exam identifies negative issues that cause the buyer to reconsider their offer price and either renegotiate the price down, or cancel the acquisition. This can waste lots of the seller\u00e2\u0080\u0099s time as the sales process has to start back from scratch.\r\n\r\n2. NOT GETTING THE CENTER PRE-QUALIFIED FOR A SBA LOAN, OR GETTING IT PRE-QUALIFIED WITH THE WRONG LENDER BEFORE YOU APPROACH POTENTIAL BUYERS. The difference in monthly loan payment between a low and a high interest SBA loan can be as high as $1,400 for a $1 million loan. When a buyer expects a lower monthly loan payment when the price is being negotiated (because it was prequalified for financing), a buyer is more willing to offer more for the center. \r\n\r\nThere are about 6k SBA lenders. Each lender is different in terms of: 1) what loan amounts they like to lend, 2) what industries they like and dislike to lend to, 3) what interest rates that like to lend at, 4) what collateral requirements they require, and 5) what experience, credit score, and liquidity after a business is acquired they want the buyer to have. Most buyers do not know which SBA lenders have made many loans to childcare centers at low interest rates, and are therefore are the best lenders to initially contact to get financing. Therefore, many buyers can waste a considerable amounts of time with the wrong lender only for the loan request to be rejected; or the buyer get unfavorable loan terms (and tries to renegotiate to lower the price and/or increase the amount of seller financing). A buyer could also try to find a new lender (therefore the transaction closing date will be delayed).\r\n\r\n(Seller should use a Loan Broker who specializes in the childcare industry to pre-qualify the center to the best lenders early in the selling process to prevent Mistake #2)\r\n\r\n1. THE SINGLE BIGGEST MISTAKE A BUSINESS OWNER CAN MAKE IS ACCEPTING AN OFFER THAT SEEMS FAIR OR EVEN REALLY ATTRACTIVE WITHOUT THE PROPER PREPARATION. When you accept an offer and establish exclusivity with a single potential buyer and begin to iron out the details, you are stuck and you have little leverage in the negotiations that occurs between the initial acceptance of an offer and the transaction closing a few months later. The good offer that you start with never goes up, but it can easily go down as the process unfolds. You may be watching the price grow smaller because of the buyer's due diligence investigation. (Most childcare center owners who want to sell, are not listed for sale by business brokers. I can help you contact them by coaching you with the most effective approaches!)\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo find the RIGHT business to buy\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo prevent a client from over-paying for a business and/or buy the WRONG business\r\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2\tTo secure a SBA loan at a lower interest rate than what the buyer could get on his/her own.", "logo": ""}}}]}
